ng. Sonnenschein shows the transformational potential of encounter between members of groups in conflict, sharing how ordinary Israelis and Palestinians coming together in an open and honest environment undergo life-changing experiences that provide concrete hope for a sustainable path to a peaceful shared existence as equals in Israel and Palestine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aArab-Israeli conflicty1993-xPeace. 0aConflict managementzIsrael. 0aJewszIsraelvInterviews. 0aMulticultural educationzIsrael. 0aPalestinian ArabszIsraelvInterviews. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aReich, Deb, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReich, Deb.1 aSaguy, Tamar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaguy, Tamar.1 aSonnenschein, Nava, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065352640uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813599250zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813599250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813599250.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065352-6  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook